          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Heading into the ho=
liday season, <i>Moana 2 </i>is tracking to crush the $125 million Wednesda=
y-Sunday haul for <i>Frozen II </i>(earned in its second weekend, following=
 its $130 million debut in 2019) to net a new Thanksgiving record. Even if =
the animated sequel ends up looking and feeling like a Disney+ series pretz=
eled into a theatrical sequel, strong 2010s nostalgia for Disney titles=E2=
=80=94think <i>Avatar: The Way of Water</i>,<i> Inside Out 2</i>, and <i>De=
adpool &amp; Wolverine</i>=E2=80=94has been kicking butt the past two years=
=2E   <br/><br/>Meanwhile, enthusiasm f=
or <i>Wicked </i>should continue to bu=
ild among fans of the Broadway show between now and opening day. Those inte=
rested in movie-specific hooks, like pop star <b>Ariana Grande </b>in a sce=
ne-stealing comic turn, will also tune in. Interestingly, <i>Gladiator II <=
/i>was essentially tied with
<i>Wicked </i>for overall interest (<u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e=
/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUSHRteG9uOS1rNTNzUkpaVHVLRT0i=
LCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9kZWFkbGluZS5jb20vMjAyNC8xMC93aWNrZWQtZ2xhZGlhdG9yLWl=
pLWJveC1vZmZpY2Utb3BlbmluZy0xMjM2MTYzMzUyLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249V2hhdCtJJTI3bS=
tIZWFyaW5nKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTElMkYxMSUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZ=
T1jdXN0b21lci5pbyIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6=
MTk3MjM5MH0/5e1dc5a8eb61b6874a6e1a73b03389df69266a3674f47282dbec820f69335dc=
6" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"s=
df">as of this writing</a></u>) among women. <br/><br/>Could the frequently=
 shirtless <b>Paul Mescal</b> and co-star <b>Pedro Pascal</b> draw otherwis=
e interested female audiences (and their male companions) away from <i>Wick=
ed </i>on opening weekend and over the holiday? Sure, but the fact that its=
 audience skewed 80 percent female didn=E2=80=99t hurt the $142 million ope=
ning of <i>The Twilight Saga: New Moon</i> in November 2009. History has sh=
own that a demographic ceiling matters less if the ceiling is high enough.<=
br/><br/>It would be encouraging if Disney=E2=80=99s first big Thanksgiving=
 hit of the 2020s weren=E2=80=99t a sequel, but alas=E2=80=A6 Hopefully, C.=
E.O.
<b>Bob Iger </b>remembers that you can=E2=80=99t (theoretically, not a pred=
iction) make $1 billion off <i>Moana 2 </i>without rolling the dice on (and=
 being satisfied with a $643 million global total for) an original movie=E2=
=80=94like, say, <i>Moana</i>, in 2016. Similarly, whether <i>Wicked: Part =
One</i> or <i>Moana 2</i> comes out on top, Universal might get more of a b=
enefit from a =E2=80=9Cnew=E2=80=9D franchise in <i>Wicked</i>. After all, =
<i>Moana 2</i>=E2=80=99s success won=E2=80=99t change the narrative over Di=
sney=E2=80=99s reliance on previously successful properties. If that=E2=80=
=99s the conversation we=E2=80=99re having on December 2, it will be good n=
ews for all invested parties.<br/></td>
